From: Jason Elie Bou Kheir <jason.boukheir@gmail.com>
Subject: [PATCH] streaming_handler: don't drop chunks with only delta.reasoning

vLLM 0.20+ emits reasoning tokens on the bare `delta.reasoning` field
(qwen3 / deepseek_r1 / etc. parsers). LiteLLM's CustomStreamWrapper
silently drops those chunks because:

  1. `handle_openai_chat_completion_chunk` reads only `delta.content`,
     so `text` is empty for reasoning-only chunks.
  2. `is_chunk_non_empty` then sees empty content + no tool calls + no
     `delta.reasoning_content` (the OLD field name) and judges the
     chunk empty, returning False. The proxy drops it before the
     client (e.g. OWUI) ever sees it.

Add the missing `delta.reasoning` check against the original upstream
chunk so reasoning-only chunks are forwarded through the existing
"copy original_chunk choices into model_response" path. The receiving
choices preserve the `reasoning` field via Pydantic `extra="allow"`.

--- a/litellm/litellm_core_utils/streaming_handler.py
+++ b/litellm/litellm_core_utils/streaming_handler.py
@@ -737,6 +737,15 @@ class CustomStreamWrapper:
                 "annotations" in model_response.choices[0].delta
                 and model_response.choices[0].delta.annotations is not None
             )
+            or (
+                # vLLM 0.20+ emits the reasoning stream on `delta.reasoning`
+                # (bare field, not `reasoning_content`). The original chunk
+                # is the only place this lives at gate-check time; the
+                # downstream copy-from-original_chunk branch preserves it.
+                response_obj.get("original_chunk") is not None
+                and len(getattr(response_obj["original_chunk"], "choices", []) or []) > 0
+                and getattr(response_obj["original_chunk"].choices[0].delta, "reasoning", None) is not None
+            )
         ):
             return True
         else:
